summary: An ordinance providing for the laying off and establishing a public street over and across that certain tract of land deeded to the City of Seattle by C.T. Conover by conveyance dated the 7th day of April, 1922, in Tract one (1) of the Plat of Conover Park, under authority of Ordinance No. 43389, and naming and designating the same as Conover Court.
